            \section{Triggers}

                \subsection{MySQL bug nÂ°61555}
                    Some triggers had to be defined to work around this well-known MySQL bug, reported in 2011: \url{https://bugs.mysql.com/bug.php?id=61555}.

                    The bug incorrectly prevents triggers with \mintinline{sql}{AFTER DELETE} from being called after an \mintinline{sql}{ON DELETE CASCADE} foreign key constraint.

                    The workaround was manually implementing triggers that reproduce the \mintinline{sql}{ON DELETE CASCADE} functionality.

                \printSQLTablepage{90_trgNotifications.sql}{notifications}
                    These triggers deal with \emph{notification generation}.

                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item \mintinline{sql}{trg_notifications_user}: generates a notification when a tracked user creates content.
                        \item \mintinline{sql}{trg_notifications_thread}: generates a notification when a post is added to a tracked thread.
                        \item \mintinline{sql}{trg_notifications_tag}: generates a notification when content with the tracked tag is created.
                    \end{itemize}

