        \chapter{Web interface}

            \section{Frontend}

                The frontend was developed using \emph{HTML5}, \emph{CSS3} and \emph{EcmaScript 5}. Good practices and popular guidelines have been followed to make sure the web pages work on all major browsers and devices without issues.

                \subsection{Bootstrap}

                    The graphical interface of the web application uses the \emph{Bootstrap} frontend library, developed by Twitter.

                    Bootstrap is a convenient and powerful \emph{CSS3}/\emph{Javascript} library that is easy to integrate in dynamic web applications. 

                    Its flexible grid system ensures responsiveness on every modern browser and device. The design of the web pages automatically adapts to the size of the browser viewport.

                    Its JavaScript-enabled features, such as \emph{modals} and \emph{navigation bars}, gratly improve the browsing experience for the user.

                \subsection{JQuery}

                    \emph{JQuery} is a very famous and popular JavaScript library that is nowadays found in most modern web pages and web applications.

                    It provides very convenient syntax for \emph{DOM manipulation} to the developer, and also offers many advanced features to improve the look and the functionality of the frontend.

                    JQuery also provides advanced \emph{AJAX-enabled} functions that load pages and sub-pages without having to refresh the web application. This feature was used extensively, alongside JQuery's animation module, to make the veeForum frontend dynamic and aesthetically pleasing.
            
